The paper discusses the importance of learning algorithms for deep architectures in statistical machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus of the paper is on handwritten character recognition, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of self-taught learning and out-of-distribution examples, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with character images and their variations, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
